I'm gonna do with you guys.

243
00:16:37.164 --> 00:16:39.583
Just give us a job painting,
leave the rest to us.

244
00:16:39.750 --> 00:16:42.085
- It was the Sistine Chapel.
- Sixteenth Chapel?

245
00:16:42.252 --> 00:16:45.088
- Sistine Chapel.
- Who painted the other 15?

246
00:16:52.596 --> 00:16:56.808
<i>Outside events meant little.
In a society changing radically by the hour…</i>

247
00:16:56.975 --> 00:17:00.229
<i>… we watched the images scatter nightly
across the TV screens.</i>

248
00:17:00.395 --> 00:17:05.317
<i>Young protesters spoke about how they were
going to change our lives and fix the world.</i>

249
00:17:05.484 --> 00:17:09.947
<i>But while they shouted their slogans,
my friends and I went to funeral services…</i>

250
00:17:10.113 --> 00:17:15.118
<i>… for the young men of Hell's Kitchen
who came back from Vietnam in body bags.</i>

251
00:17:15.285 --> 00:17:18.622
<i>We viewed with skepticism
the faces on television…</i>

252
00:17:18.789 --> 00:17:22.251
<i>… those protected by money
and upper-middle-class standing.</i>

253
00:17:24.461 --> 00:17:30.050
<i>A growing army of feminists marched
across the country demanding equality.</i>

254
00:17:30.217 --> 00:17:34.179
<i>Yet our mothers cooked and cared for men
who abused them mentally and physically.</i>

255
00:17:36.348 --> 00:17:39.810
<i>For me and my friends,
these developments carried no weight.</i>

256
00:17:39.977 --> 00:17:44.773
<i>They might as well have occurred
in another country, in another century.</i>

257
00:17:44.940 --> 00:17:46.942
<i>Our attention was elsewhere.</i>

258
00:17:47.109 --> 00:17:49.945
<i>We sat with Father Bobby
in a hospital ward, visiting John…</i>

259
00:17:50.112 --> 00:17:52.322
<i>… hoping he'd recover
from a punctured lung…</i>

260
00:17:52.489 --> 00:17:55.158
<i>… a gift from one of his mother's
overzealous boyfriends.</i>

261
00:17:55.325 --> 00:17:58.787
I hope you like these.
You better not tell me you don't.

262
00:17:58.954 --> 00:18:00.706
Okay.

263
00:18:03.083 --> 00:18:05.168
<i>Father Bobby
didn't let that situation rest.</i>

264
