310
00:20:23.473 --> 00:20:26.476
What happens is our business,
not yours, okay?

311
00:20:26.643 --> 00:20:28.478
You gotta stay tough to be tough.

312
00:20:28.645 --> 00:20:31.398
Guy smells it when you're weak,
eat you like a salad.

313
00:20:31.565 --> 00:20:36.278
You see that street? That street is the dish
of life and you boys are appetizers.

314
00:20:36.445 --> 00:20:39.823
Somebody gonna come along,
eat you up and forget about you by dessert.

315
00:20:39.990 --> 00:20:42.409
Take it easy, fat man.
It was just a stickball game.

316
00:20:42.576 --> 00:20:45.579
Yeah, but going soft is a habit,
you know?

317
00:20:45.746 --> 00:20:48.874
You have to keep yourself mean
and cut your life around it.

318
00:20:49.499 --> 00:20:53.670
All right, calm down. It's like hanging out
with fucking Confucius over here.

319
00:20:53.837 --> 00:20:55.714
Be funny, limp dick.

320
00:20:55.881 --> 00:20:59.843
This is just free advice from me to you.
Take it or throw it away. It don't matter.

321
00:21:00.010 --> 00:21:01.678
Thanks a lot, fat man.

322
00:21:03.513 --> 00:21:06.141
<i>In truth, we were all surprised
by Michael's actions.</i>

323
00:21:06.308 --> 00:21:08.018
<i>But in his mind, losing that game…</i>

324
00:21:08.185 --> 00:21:11.104
<i>… and handing a feeling of victory
to a girl in a wheelchair…</i>

325
00:21:11.271 --> 00:21:13.523
<i>… was more than the right thing to do.</i>

326
00:21:22.324 --> 00:21:23.700
Come on, let's go swimming.

327
00:21:23.867 --> 00:21:25.994
<i>The temperature
topped out at 98 degrees…</i>

328
00:21:26.161 --> 00:21:28.497
<i>… on the day our lives
were forever altered.</i>

329
00:21:28.663 --> 00:21:30.123
I'm frying like an egg up here.

330
00:21:30.290 --> 00:21:34.377
I say we get some butter rolls, sodas,
head down to the docks, cool off.

331
00:21:34.544 --> 00:21:37.756
- Can't you feel the breeze?
- What breeze? We're surrounded by a wall.

332
00:21:37.923 --> 00:21:41.718
- The devil couldn't even stand this heat.
- I'm trying to get my burn.

333
00:21:41.885 --> 00:21:43.428
It's 98 degrees.

334
00:21:43.595 --> 00:21:46.264
- There's some breeze.
- It's a hot breeze.

335
00:21:46.431 --> 00:21:48.517
We haven't hit the hot dog vendor
in a couple weeks.

336
00:21:48.683 --> 00:21:51.812
I don't know, Mikey.
That cart guy ain't like the others.

337
00:21:51.978 --> 00:21:55.816
I mean, he gets pretty pissed,
like crazy when you try to take him off.

338
00:21:55.982 --> 00:21:59.986
We can eat hot dogs
or we can eat air. Choose.

339
00:22:01.738 --> 00:22:03.323
Air is probably safer, Mike.

340
00:22:03.490 --> 00:22:05.784
A hot dog ain't worth
bleeding over, Mikey.

341
00:22:05.951 --> 00:22:09.329
- Yeah, but anyway, whose turn was it?
- Yours.

342
00:22:09.496 --> 00:22:11.998
- Yeah, it's yours.
- Mine? It's not my turn.

343
00:22:12.165 --> 00:22:13.917
- Yes, it is.
- I went like last month.

344
00:22:14.084 --> 00:22:15.377
- He went—
- You never went.

345
00:22:15.544 --> 00:22:17.295
- Last month.
- I went right after him.

346
00:22:17.462 --> 00:22:18.713
- I'm not going.
- Why?

347
00:22:18.880 --> 00:22:21.758
It's too hot.
If I walk down the stairs, I'll pass out.

348
00:22:25.554 --> 00:22:27.597
Mustard, onions, no soda.

349
00:22:27.764 --> 00:22:28.807
I know you.

350
00:22:29.432 --> 00:22:31.017
I look like a lot of people.

351
00:22:31.685 --> 00:22:32.811
<i>The scam was simple.</i>

352
00:22:33.228 --> 00:22:36.606
<i>I was to walk up to the hot dog vendor
and order what I wanted.</i>

353
00:22:36.773 --> 00:22:40.610
<i>The vendor would then hand me my hot dog
and watch as I ran off without paying.</i>

354
00:22:40.777 --> 00:22:43.780
<i>This left the vendor with two choices,
neither very appealing.</i>

355
00:22:43.947 --> 00:22:47.367
<i>He could stand his ground and
swallow his loss, or he could give chase.</i>

356
00:22:47.534 --> 00:22:52.289
<i>The second forces him to abandon the cart,
where my friends could feast in his absence.</i>

357
00:22:55.292 --> 00:22:56.543
Uh, I'm gonna need two napkins.

358
00:22:58.461 --> 00:23:00.797
Pay my money, thief!

359
00:23:03.300 --> 00:23:04.801
Yes!

360
00:23:07.429 --> 00:23:10.015
- Ketchup.
<i>- I took it from him and ran.</i>

361
00:23:10.181 --> 00:23:14.519
<i>I scooted past Tommy Mug's Dry Cleaners
and Armond's Shoe Repair.</i>

362
00:23:14.686 --> 00:23:18.523
<i>The vendor gave chase, a wooden-handled
pronged fork in one hand.</i>

363
00:23:18.982 --> 00:23:21.318
All right, all right.
Oh, you're gonna give me two?

364
00:23:31.953 --> 00:23:33.830
These things are heavier than they look.

365
00:23:33.997 --> 00:23:36.875
Genius, it's the gas tanks
that keep the food hot.

366
00:23:37.042 --> 00:23:39.169
They're heavier than shit.

367
00:23:39.336 --> 00:23:41.713
Think we can push it, the three of us?

368
00:23:41.880 --> 00:23:43.173
Push it where, huh?

369
00:23:43.340 --> 00:23:46.176
Couple of blocks.
It'll be a nice surprise for the guy…

370
00:23:46.343 --> 00:23:50.013
… when he comes back from
chasing Shakes not to find his cart.

371
00:24:10.033 --> 00:24:12.285
<i>The vendor tired at 47th and 9th.</i>

372
00:24:12.452 --> 00:24:14.204
<i>I was on the other side of the street.</i>

373
00:24:16.206 --> 00:24:18.792
<i>He was beat, but not beaten.</i>

374
00:24:18.959 --> 00:24:21.294
<i>He could go 10 minutes more
just on hate alone.</i>

375
00:24:21.753 --> 00:24:25.256
Come on. Give it up.

376
00:24:37.978 --> 00:24:39.229
What's wrong, Mikey?

377
00:24:40.397 --> 00:24:44.192
Shakes is taking too long.
He should've been back by now.

378
00:24:44.359 --> 00:24:46.069
He'll be fine. He's Shakes.

379
00:24:48.863 --> 00:24:51.741
You guys were supposed
to take the hot dogs, not the wagon.

380
00:24:51.992 --> 00:24:53.785
- Now he tells us.
- He's coming fast.

381
00:24:53.952 --> 00:24:55.203
- He still near?
- Let's go!

382
00:24:55.370 --> 00:24:57.664
I got a plan.
Come on, over by the subway.

383
00:24:58.206 --> 00:25:00.917
<i>The plan, as it turned out,
was as simple and as dumb…</i>

384
00:25:01.084 --> 00:25:02.377
<i>… as anything we had ever done.</i>

385
00:25:02.544 --> 00:25:05.046
<i>We'd hold the cart on the top edge
of the stairwell…</i>

386
00:25:05.213 --> 00:25:07.215
<i>… lean it downward
and wait for the vendor.</i>

387
00:25:07.382 --> 00:25:09.634
<i>We'd let it go
the second he grabbed the handles.</i>

388
00:25:09.801 --> 00:25:13.263
<i>We'd leave the scene as he struggled
to ease the cart back on the sidewalk.</i>

389
00:25:13.430 --> 00:25:15.765
<i>To this day, I don't know why we did it.</i>

390
00:25:15.932 --> 00:25:18.268
<i>But we would all pay a price.</i>

391
00:25:18.435 --> 00:25:21.646
<i>It only took a minute,
but in that minute, everything changed.</i>

392
00:25:21.813 --> 00:25:24.482
Guys, I can't hold it! I can't hold it!

393
00:25:24.649 --> 00:25:26.359
- Don't let go!
