Uh…

1357
01:38:54.680 --> 01:38:56.890
It's like pulling teeth.

1358
01:38:58.851 --> 01:39:01.603
I should've pinned the questions
to his shirt.

1359
01:39:01.770 --> 01:39:05.899
And tell me, then at dinner, you, uh—

1360
01:39:06.400 --> 01:39:09.111
Strike that. Uh…

1361
01:39:12.239 --> 01:39:13.824
<i>What time did you have lunch?</i>

1362
01:39:15.784 --> 01:39:18.245
What time, Mrs. Salinas,
did you have lunch?

1363
01:39:18.412 --> 01:39:19.913
Objection, Your Honor.

1364
01:39:20.914 --> 01:39:22.541
What Mrs. Salinas did on the day…

1365
01:39:22.708 --> 01:39:25.127
… has nothing to do with
what she saw on the night.

1366
01:39:25.294 --> 01:39:27.296
How much she had to drink does,
Your Honor.

1367
01:39:27.463 --> 01:39:28.589
Overruled.

1368
01:39:29.840 --> 01:39:33.969
Ahem. Mrs. Salinas,
what time, uh, did you have lunch?

1369
01:39:34.428 --> 01:39:35.679
About 1:30.

1370
01:39:35.846 --> 01:39:37.347
And what did you have for lunch?

1371
01:39:37.514 --> 01:39:42.519
It was a while ago. Um, probably a salad.
I like to eat a little light in the day.

1372
01:39:42.686 --> 01:39:45.939
A martini, two glasses of wine and a salad.
Is that correct?

1373
01:39:46.106 --> 01:39:47.733
Yes, that's right.

1374
01:39:47.900 --> 01:39:52.613
And then you had wine at dinner
about six hours later. Is that right?

1375
01:39:52.779 --> 01:39:55.491
- Yes, that's right.
- How much wine did you have to drink…

1376
01:39:55.657 --> 01:39:58.243
… by the time my clients allegedly
walked into McHales?

1377
01:39:58.410 --> 01:40:02.915
- Two glasses.
- Would you say that four glasses of wine…

1378
01:40:03.081 --> 01:40:06.752
… and a martini within a six-hour period
is a lot for you to drink?

1379
01:40:07.336 --> 01:40:08.587
Yes, it is. Yes.

1380
01:40:08.754 --> 01:40:11.465
Aha. Sure.

1381
01:40:13.509 --> 01:40:19.556
And, uh, had you ever heard a gun fired
prior to the night in question?

1382
01:40:19.723 --> 01:40:20.974
No.

1383
01:40:22.392 --> 01:40:24.144
How would you describe the sound?

1384
01:40:24.311 --> 01:40:27.064
It was loud. Like fireworks loud.

1385
01:40:28.607 --> 01:40:32.611
- Did the sound, uh, frighten you?
- Very much.

1386
01:40:32.778 --> 01:40:35.405
Did you close your eyes?

1387
01:40:36.740 --> 01:40:39.785
At first, um, until the shooting stopped.
Then I opened them.

1388
01:40:39.952 --> 01:40:44.248
Did you think the men who did the shooting
were going to kill everybody in McHales?

1389
01:40:44.414 --> 01:40:48.627
Well, I really didn't know what to think.
I just knew that the man had been shot.

1390
01:40:48.794 --> 01:40:53.549
Did you think you might be shot dead
by the two cold-blooded killers?

1391
01:40:54.216 --> 01:40:55.259
Yes, yes, I did.

1392
01:40:55.425 --> 01:40:59.888
Yet despite that fear,
despite that risk to your life…

1393
01:41:00.055 --> 01:41:05.018
… you looked at their faces, uh,
as they left?

1394
01:41:05.185 --> 01:41:07.020
- Yes, I did.
- Is that correct?

1395
01:41:08.564 --> 01:41:09.648
Yes, I did.

1396
01:41:10.232 --> 01:41:16.572
Did you look at their faces?
Did you really, really look, Mrs. Salinas?

1397
01:41:17.573 --> 01:41:20.284
I glanced at them when they walked by,
but I did see them.

1398
01:41:20.450 --> 01:41:24.621
You glanced? You didn't look?

1399
01:41:25.622 --> 01:41:26.832
I saw them.

1400
01:41:27.874 --> 01:41:31.837
You glanced at them, Mrs. Salinas.
You glanced at them through the eyes…

1401
01:41:32.004 --> 01:41:37.926
… of a very frightened woman
who maybe had too much to drink.

1402
01:41:38.093 --> 01:41:40.512
- Objection, Your Honor.
- No need, Your Honor.

1403
01:41:40.679 --> 01:41:42.306
I have no further questions.

1404
01:41:42.472 --> 01:41:45.809
Thank you, Mrs. Salinas.
You may step down.

1405
01:41:48.937 --> 01:41:51.231
<i>It was 6:15 on Sunday morning.</i>

1406
01:41:51.398 --> 01:41:54.526
<i>Frank Magcicco worked out of
a homicide unit in Brooklyn.</i>

1407
01:41:54.693 --> 01:41:58.113
<i>He was a first-grade detective
with an honest name and a solid reputation.</i>

1408
01:41:58.280 --> 01:42:00.240
<i>He was also King Benny's nephew.</i>

1409
01:42:00.741 --> 01:42:03.535
<i>Nick Davenport was with Internal Affairs.</i>

1410
01:42:03.702 --> 01:42:06.705
<i>He was ambitious and wanted
to make captain before he hit 40.</i>

1411
01:42:06.872 --> 01:42:10.834
<i>He knew the fastest way up the track was
to reel in a maximum amount of dirty cops…</i>

1412
01:42:11.001 --> 01:42:12.544
<i>… in a minimum amount of time.</i>

1413
01:42:12.711 --> 01:42:16.798
- Frank, what is this shit?
- Hey, if I were you, I'd do what the kid says.

1414
01:42:16.965 --> 01:42:19.968
Make this one, have breakfast once a month
with the commissioner.

1415
01:42:20.135 --> 01:42:23.722
You got a real hard-on for this Styler guy.
What's your beef with him?

1416
01:42:23.889 --> 01:42:25.891
- One more thing.
- Jeez, I can't wait.

1417
01:42:26.058 --> 01:42:29.811
It's simple. No one knows
who fed you this information.

1418
01:42:29.978 --> 01:42:32.022
- And I mean nobody.
- How did you get it?

1419
01:42:32.189 --> 01:42:35.692
It fell into my lap,
just like it's gonna fall into yours.

1420
01:42:42.866 --> 01:42:44.910
Christ almighty.

1421
01:42:51.583 --> 01:42:53.293
Got everything in here but a confession.

1422
01:42:53.460 --> 01:42:55.212
I thought I'd leave that up to you.

1423
01:42:55.379 --> 01:42:58.924
- My preference is you beat it out of him.
- There's even surveillance photos.

1424
01:42:59.508 --> 01:43:02.594
Piece of shit's pulling in 5 grand a month
ripping off pushers.

1425
01:43:02.761 --> 01:43:04.221
Has been for about three years.

1426
01:43:04.388 --> 01:43:06.306
- More like four.
- He ain't gonna see five.

1427
01:43:06.473 --> 01:43:10.060
- So you got enough for conviction?
- That ain't up to me. That's up to a jury.

1428
01:43:13.772 --> 01:43:15.982
Show the jury this.

1429
01:43:18.110 --> 01:43:20.404
- What do you got there, Ness?
- Three weeks ago…

1430
01:43:20.570 --> 01:43:23.490
… the body of a drug dealer
named Indian Red Lopez was found…

1431
01:43:23.657 --> 01:43:26.576
… in an alley in Jackson Heights.
Three bullets in his head…

1432
01:43:26.743 --> 01:43:28.870
- … nothing in his pockets.
- With you so far.

1433
01:43:29.037 --> 01:43:31.665
This is the gun that killed him
and these are the shells.

1434
01:43:32.165 --> 01:43:35.335
And, uh, what's behind
door number three?

1435
01:43:35.877 --> 01:43:38.463
The prints on the gun
belong to Adam Styler.

1436
01:43:42.384 --> 01:43:44.219
- Do me a favor, would you?
- What's that?

1437
01:43:44.386 --> 01:43:47.472
If I ever make it onto your shit list,
give me a call.

1438
01:43:47.639 --> 01:43:49.683
Give me a chance to apologize.

1439
01:43:50.434 --> 01:43:54.104
So you need anything else, you talk to
Frank. He knows how to get ahold of me.

1440
01:43:54.271 --> 01:43:57.899
Take care of yourself, kid.
Water gets choppy out your way.

1441
01:43:58.066 --> 01:43:59.484
I'll do what I can.

1442
01:44:00.694 --> 01:44:02.320
Hey, Ness…

1443
01:44:02.654 --> 01:44:04.990
… did you ever think of becoming a cop?

1444
01:44:05.282 --> 01:44:07.033
And leave the good guys?

1445
01:44:14.583 --> 01:44:16.084
The body of Christ.

1446
01:44:17.502 --> 01:44:19.379
The body of Christ.

1447
01:44:20.964 --> 01:44:22.841
The body of Christ.

1448
01:44:24.176 --> 01:44:26.344
- The body of Christ.
- Amen.

1449
01:44:28.680 --> 01:44:30.807
- The body of Christ.
- Amen.

1450
01:44:32.684 --> 01:44:34.978
- The body of Christ.
- Amen.

1451
01:44:35.145 --> 01:44:37.147
The body of Chri—

1452
01:44:45.989 --> 01:44:47.491
Amen.

1453
01:44:50.202 --> 01:44:52.412
The body of Christ.

1454
01:44:55.040 --> 01:44:57.167
<i>Michael had done all
that could be expected…</i>

1455
01:44:57.334 --> 01:45:00.712
<i>… of an assistant district attorney
seeking a conviction.</i>

1456
01:45:00.879 --> 01:45:05.675
<i>He had a forensic expert detail the make
and caliber of the gun that killed Nokes.</i>

1457
01:45:05.842 --> 01:45:08.637
<i>He just never had the murder weapon
to present as evidence…</i>

1458
01:45:08.804 --> 01:45:11.306
<i>… and he never gave the jury
a motive for the murder.</i>

1459
01:45:12.224 --> 01:45:14.601
<i>The tension of his task,
the hours he was working…</i>

1460
01:45:14.768 --> 01:45:17.729
<i>… and the uncertainty about the outcome
weighed heavily on him.</i>

1461
01:45:17.896 --> 01:45:19.022
Did you see their faces?

1462
01:45:19.189 --> 01:45:22.317
Yes, I looked at them
and they looked at me.

1463
01:45:22.484 --> 01:45:23.902
Did they say anything to you?

1464
01:45:24.069 --> 01:45:26.321
They just looked at me
and walked out of McHales.

1465
01:45:26.488 --> 01:45:28.657
Are you sure the defendants
killed Sean Nokes?

1466
01:45:28.824 --> 01:45:30.534
I know they killed him.

1467
01:45:30.700 --> 01:45:33.453
<i>If the plan worked,
it would be everyone's success.</i>

1468
01:45:33.620 --> 01:45:35.997
<i>If it failed, the fault would fall to Michael.</i>

1469
01:45:39.251 --> 01:45:43.213
<i>Father Bobby Carrillo, the priest
with the best hook shot on the West Side…</i>

1470
01:45:43.380 --> 01:45:47.634
<i>… remained the key to a plan that called
for all involved to get away with murder.</i>

1471
01:45:47.801 --> 01:45:51.429
Did you turn around, look behind you,
when you heard the shooting, Mr. Carson?

1472
01:45:51.596 --> 01:45:53.223
Why didn't you turn around?

1473
01:45:53.390 --> 01:45:57.269
- I was concerned for my companion's safety.
- Mr. Carson, did the two individuals…

1474
01:45:57.435 --> 01:45:59.104
- … threaten you in any way?
- No.

1475
01:45:59.271 --> 01:46:03.775
Did they threaten anyone in
McHales Restaurant, as far as you know?

1476
01:46:03.942 --> 01:46:05.443
I didn't see it, but I know it.

1477
01:46:05.610 --> 01:46:08.321
If you didn't see the defendants
shoot the guy…

1478
01:46:08.488 --> 01:46:12.576
<i>… then how do you know
it was the defendants that shot the guy?</i>

1479
01:46:34.472 --> 01:46:36.641
So, what's the emergency?

1480
01:46:40.103 --> 01:46:41.980
Shakes shouldn't have sent you.
Too risky.

1481
01:46:42.147 --> 01:46:46.610
Hey, nobody sent me.
I wanted to see you.

1482
01:46:47.903 --> 01:46:49.321
Why?

1483
01:46:50.280 --> 01:46:53.033
Shakes met with Father Bobby
two weeks ago.

1484
01:46:53.199 --> 01:46:57.245
- He hasn't heard from him since.
- It's not an overnight decision for him.

1485
01:47:00.498 --> 01:47:04.502
- What if he doesn't testify?
- Then we got a very serious problem.

1486
01:47:19.434 --> 01:47:22.395
Have Shakes talk to Father Bobby again.

1487
01:47:23.313 --> 01:47:26.983
Have him tell him the whole story.
He'll know what that means.

1488
01:47:27.150 --> 01:47:28.610
He already has.

1489
01:47:30.362 --> 01:47:31.655
What?

1490
01:47:33.949 --> 01:47:36.451
I was with him
when he talked to Father Bobby.

1491
01:47:39.245 --> 01:47:41.164
I heard everything, Michael.

1492
01:47:51.091 --> 01:47:52.842
So you know.

1493
01:47:55.095 --> 01:47:56.638
Yeah.

1494
01:48:00.266 --> 01:48:02.352
If only you told me.

1495
01:48:06.731 --> 01:48:09.442
I think things could've been different…

1496
01:48:11.236 --> 01:48:13.530
… if you could've talked.

1497
01:48:17.742 --> 01:48:21.162
Maybe— Maybe we—

1498
01:48:23.957 --> 01:48:25.542
Maybe—

1499
01:48:31.423 --> 01:48:32.882
And I—

1500
01:48:49.107 --> 01:48:50.150
Hey, Sid, how you doing?

1501
01:48:50.316 --> 01:48:52.861
Carmen, that diet is working.
I don't care what anybody says.

1502
01:48:55.572 --> 01:48:57.574
You still have a thing for Doris Day.

1503
01:48:57.741 --> 01:48:59.993
She's a good woman.

1504
01:49:00.952 --> 01:49:03.121
You know the <i>strega?</i>

1505
01:49:03.288 --> 01:49:06.458
Hard to miss a lady with four warts
and only one eye.

1506
01:49:06.624 --> 01:49:09.335
She needs the heads.

1507
01:49:09.502 --> 01:49:10.545
Salvatore.

1508
01:49:10.712 --> 01:49:14.174
<i>And when forever is through</i>

1509
01:49:14.507 --> 01:49:16.801
Take this to the witch.

1510
01:49:17.552 --> 01:49:19.304
Now, why does she need the heads?

1511
01:49:19.471 --> 01:49:22.223
- She takes the eyes.
- Oh. Wonderful.

1512
01:49:22.390 --> 01:49:26.227
Puts them in a bowl
and mixes them with water and oil.

1513
01:49:26.603 --> 01:49:27.896
And then?

1514
01:49:29.314 --> 01:49:31.983
People get headaches, they go to her.

1515
01:49:32.150 --> 01:49:37.280
She looks into their eyes and tells them
who is wishing the headaches.

1516
01:49:37.447 --> 01:49:41.993
She says a few words
and the headaches go away.

1517
01:49:42.160 --> 01:49:46.414
Once in a while, the person who wished
the headaches goes away too.

1518
01:49:46.915 --> 01:49:50.835
This guy, Addison,
the one who works for the mayor…

1519
01:49:51.002 --> 01:49:53.671
… he quits his job in two weeks.

1520
01:49:53.838 --> 01:49:57.258
He don't want nobody to know
what kind of a guy he is.

1521
01:49:57.425 --> 01:50:01.679
He don't want nobody to see
pictures of him they shouldn't see.

1522
01:50:02.347 --> 01:50:04.808
- He knows this?
- He will.

1523
01:50:05.517 --> 01:50:07.852
The boys he buys for parties
are expensive.

1524
01:50:08.019 --> 01:50:12.607
Now, Addison makes good money,
but he don't make real money.

1525
01:50:13.024 --> 01:50:14.192
How much does he owe?

1526
01:50:14.359 --> 01:50:18.571
Eight grand with a heavy vig.
I paid that off.

1527
01:50:18.738 --> 01:50:20.240
You paid?

1528
01:50:20.698 --> 01:50:23.618
Addison's debts belong to me now.

1529
01:50:24.452 --> 01:50:27.497
- You hate debts.
- I hate Addison.

1530
01:50:29.541 --> 01:50:33.044
We're in the dirty end of the field now.
That's where I play.

1531
01:50:33.211 --> 01:50:35.296
And I like to play alone.

1532
01:50:35.463 --> 01:50:41.052
You're a nice kid. You always were.
Don't let this change it.

1533
01:50:53.565 --> 01:50:56.568
<i>His mother named him
Edward Goldenberg Robinson…</i>

1534
01:50:56.734 --> 01:50:58.611
<i>… after her favorite actor.</i>

1535
01:50:58.778 --> 01:51:00.613
<i>To continue the Hollywood connection…</i>

1536
01:51:00.780 --> 01:51:03.324
<i>… Eddie Robinson took the street name
Little Caesar…</i>

1537
01:51:03.491 --> 01:51:06.744
<i>… as he made his way up the ranks
of the lucrative drug trade.</i>

1538
01:51:06.911 --> 01:51:10.665
<i>He had a 12-year-old son
in a private school in upstate New York.</i>

1539
01:51:10.832 --> 01:51:13.251
<i>He named him Rizzo,
after his youngest brother…</i>

1540
01:51:13.418 --> 01:51:16.880
<i>… who died while in the custody
of the Wilkinson Home for Boys.</i>

1541
01:51:17.046 --> 01:51:19.549
I want you to give me some money.

1542
01:51:19.716 --> 01:51:24.637
All right. I'll play along.
How long before you pay it back?

1543
01:51:24.804 --> 01:51:28.516
I ain't paying it back. Somebody else is.

1544
01:51:30.810 --> 01:51:34.272
- This somebody I know?
- Your little brother knew him.

1545
01:51:35.148 --> 01:51:36.316
Rizzo?

1546
01:51:36.482 --> 01:51:37.817
Mm-hm.

1547
01:51:38.526 --> 01:51:40.111
How did he know Rizzo?

1548
01:51:40.278 --> 01:51:44.991
Henry Addison was a guard
in a upstate reform school.

1549
01:51:45.158 --> 01:51:49.370
He was there the same time as Rizzo,
before and after he died.

1550
01:51:52.332 --> 01:51:53.958
Bip.

1551
01:51:55.168 --> 01:51:58.671
Count out $8000, put it in an envelope.

1552
01:52:03.843 --> 01:52:06.095
You, uh, go back a long time, old man.

1553
01:52:07.305 --> 01:52:08.932
Old men always do.

1554
01:52:09.307 --> 01:52:11.976
Ran with the guineas
back when the guineas were tough.

1555
01:52:12.143 --> 01:52:14.395
I ran when I could.

1556
01:52:14.771 --> 01:52:16.356
Looked good doing it too.

1557
01:52:19.192 --> 01:52:23.988
Gave the business some style,
some class.

1558
01:52:24.197 --> 01:52:28.576
Made it a call for respect
the way you wore it, the way you talked it.

1559
01:52:29.327 --> 01:52:31.829
I always liked that about you.

1560
01:52:31.996 --> 01:52:35.416
I'm no help to you. My tailor is dead.

1561
01:52:42.340 --> 01:52:46.678
I'll look up our friend
and collect the money he owes me.

1562
01:52:46.844 --> 01:52:49.013
He owes you something
more than money.

1563
01:52:49.514 --> 01:52:51.516
Ain't nothing worth more than the green.

1564
01:52:52.058 --> 01:52:55.353
- This is.
- What, old man?

1565
01:52:55.561 --> 01:52:58.064
What's this guy owe
that means more than dollars?

1566
01:52:58.231 --> 01:53:02.485
He owes you Rizzo.
He's the man that killed your brother.

1567
01:53:11.828 --> 01:53:14.205
They said he died of pneumonia.

1568
01:53:14.372 --> 01:53:16.332
They said.

1569
01:53:22.755 --> 01:53:24.590
What is the relevance of this?

1570
01:53:24.757 --> 01:53:27.635
So Ralph Ferguson
is a Sunday school teacher.

1571
01:53:27.802 --> 01:53:31.222
I don't know, counsel.
What you're asking is highly unusual.

1572
01:53:31.389 --> 01:53:36.436
I understand that, Your Honor.
Again, I need to put a face to the victim.

1573
01:53:36.602 --> 01:53:39.647
Otherwise it's just another name
in the obituaries.

1574
01:53:40.732 --> 01:53:42.483
Mr. Snyder, any objections?

1575
01:53:44.402 --> 01:53:46.446
I don't have a problem with it.

1576
01:53:46.988 --> 01:53:51.326
Your Honor, the prosecution would like
to call Ralph Ferguson to the stand.

1577
01:54:17.226 --> 01:54:19.479
- Good morning, Mr. Ferguson.
- Good morning.

1578
01:54:19.645 --> 01:54:22.690
Thank you for coming,
I realize for you it's been a long trip.

1579
01:54:23.608 --> 01:54:26.152
I'm just sorry it had to be
for something like this.

1580
01:54:27.111 --> 01:54:29.030
You and the victim
were such good friends.

1581
01:54:29.197 --> 01:54:32.325
I think your testimony as a character
witness will be very valuable.

1582
01:54:32.492 --> 01:54:35.536
We were great friends.
It would be hard to find a better friend.

1583
01:54:36.162 --> 01:54:40.500
